net.sf.mmm.util.collection.base

Class TreeNodeSimple<VALUE>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.mmm.util.collection.base.AbstractGenericTreeNode<NODE,NODE>
      • net.sf.mmm.util.collection.base.AbstractTreeNode<TreeNodeSimple<VALUE>>
        • net.sf.mmm.util.collection.base.TreeNodeSimple<VALUE>
  • Type Parameters:
    VALUE - is the generic type of the value contained in each node.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    GenericTreeNode<TreeNodeSimple<VALUE>,TreeNodeSimple<VALUE>>, Node<TreeNodeSimple<VALUE>>, TreeNode<TreeNodeSimple<VALUE>>, AttributeReadValue<VALUE>, AttributeWriteValue<VALUE>, Pojo

    public class TreeNodeSimple<VALUE>
extends AbstractTreeNode<TreeNodeSimple<VALUE>>
implements AttributeWriteValue<VALUE>, Pojo
    This is a simple but generic implementation of TreeNode. It can carry any kind of value that can be set externally.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)
